long_desc.thetext:
Further details:

in playground 

var a= new qx.ui.form.TextField("          ");
this.getRoot().add(a, {left: 40, top: 30});

permits the the access to the field (at least in the left side), while 

var a= new qx.ui.form.TextField("");
this.getRoot().add(a, {left: 40, top: 30});

does not permit any access. 
In other terms, it is possible to click only in the filled part, while in the rest of the widget the mouse click does not have effect.

I overcome the problem setting a backgroud to the content element, as in
this.myText.getContentElement().setStyle("backgroundImage","url('images/layout/blank.png')");
where blank.png is an small trasparent image. I am preatty sure it is not the best way, but maybe it can help.

It seems to me that this issue was fixed by a commit after 2009-04-15, the current trunk (r18997) has not this issue. So I set status to invalid.

