I have tried this, but the playground doesn't show the described issue:
var a= new qx.ui.form.TextField("");
this.getRoot().add(a, {left: 40, top: 30});

Reopen bug. A TextField in a Toolbar is unreachable by mouse:

var toolbar = new qx.ui.toolbar.ToolBar();
toolbar.add(new qx.ui.form.TextField());

var doc = this.getRoot();
doc.add(toolbar, {left: 100, top: 50, right: 100});

Here is a code snippet to fix the issue with an affected TextField:

var toolbar = new qx.ui.toolbar.ToolBar();
var textfield = new qx.ui.form.TextField();
toolbar.add(textfield);

// IE8 in standard mode needs some extra love here to receive events.
if (qx.core.Variant.isSet("qx.client", "mshtml"))
{
  textfield.getContentElement().setStyle("backgroundImage",
    "url(" + qx.util.ResourceManager.toUri("qx/static/blank.gif") + ")"
  );
}

var doc = this.getRoot();
doc.add(toolbar, {left: 100, top: 50, right: 100});
